{
  "stem": "151.2",
  "chunk_idx": 1,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 3.6,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 12,
      "text": "Then she came back, and was going to share it with the five of us.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 13,
      "text": "In the beginning, we shared.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 14,
      "text": "But later on, as time went on and we were starving, whoever was up front had some of the liquid.",
      "word_count": 20
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 15,
      "text": "By the time the bowl reached the fourth and the fifth prisoner, there was nothing.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 16,
      "text": "And so from then on, it became a fight every time we did the lineup.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 17,
      "text": "Who's going to stand up front?",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 18,
      "text": "And who's going to be in the back ?",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "And then later we found out-- without any warning-- Dr.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "Mengele arrived after lineup and was selecting for the gas chambers.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "So every morning and every afternoon, you had to figure out where you want to stand.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "You want to fight your way to the front of lineup, because you're so hungry that you may not make it to the afternoon lineup.",
      "word_count": 25
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "Or you will manage to survive until the afternoon, then you really want to be in the back and hide from Mengele.",
      "word_count": 22
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "In the afternoon.",
      "word_count": 3
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "In the afternoon lineup, they brought back these barrels with a similar liquid.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "They called it soup.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "And we received a slice of bread.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "And I remember on Sundays, they gave us either a slice of horse meat salami, or they gave us a little bit of margarine.",
      "word_count": 24
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "You had to put your hands out like this.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "They slapped the margarine there.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "Or, occasionally, they gave us a spoonful of a marmalade, which later we found out was made of sugar beets.",
      "word_count": 20
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "Something black, like molasses.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "And I will never forget the first day, when they gave us this molasses, and they slapped it into our hand, my little sister Clara went like this.",
      "word_count": 28
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "Threw it away, then she wiped her hand and shivered.",
      "word_count": 10
    }
  ],
